In 2014, Jordan Freeman Group], a subsidiary of ZOOM, officially released the title amongst other Knowledge Adventure titles, having secured the exclusive rights to upgrade and re-release the company's back-catalog to play on modern machines.Some copies of the game come in hexagon-shaped packaging.